SIMPLE: underrun
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underrun
<hw>Un`der*run"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To run or pass
under;</def> <specif>especially</specif> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <def>to
pass along and under, as a cable, for the purpose of taking it in, or of
examining it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The cable passes over the bows and stern of the boat
used, while the men haul the boat along by pulling upon the
cable.</note> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To underrun a hose</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>to
lift it up at one end, then walk along shifting one hand after another
so that the water will run out.</cd> -- <col><b>To underrun a
tackle</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>to separate its parts and put
them in order.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undersail</ent>⟦br⟧
